=head1 NAME

restart-browsers - Restart browsers

=head1 VERSION

This document describes version 0.008 of restart-browsers (from Perl distribution App-BrowserUtils), released on 2020-06-13.

=head1 SYNOPSIS

Usage:

 % restart-browsers [--chrome-cmd-json=s] [--chrome-cmd=s]
     [--config-path=path | -c] [--config-profile=profile | -P] [--debug]
     [--dry-run] [--firefox-cmd-json=s] [--firefox-cmd=s] [--format=name]
     [--json] [--log-level=level] [--(no)naked-res] [--no-config | -C]
     [--no-env] [--no-restart-chrome] [--no-restart-firefox]
     [--no-restart-opera] [--no-restart-vivaldi] [--norestart-chrome]
     [--norestart-firefox] [--norestart-opera] [--norestart-vivaldi]
     [--opera-cmd-json=s] [--opera-cmd=s] [--page-result[=program]] [-q]
     [--quiet] [--quiet-arg] [--restart-chrome] [--restart-firefox]
     [--restart-opera] [--restart-vivaldi] [--trace] [--verbose]
     [--view-result[=program]] [--vivaldi-cmd-json=s] [--vivaldi-cmd=s]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

For each of the requested browser, first check whether browser processes (that
run the current user) exist. If they do then terminate the browser first. After
that, start the browser again.

Example on the CLI:

 % restart-browsers --restart-firefox

To customize command:

 % restart-browsers --start-firefox --firefox-cmd 'firefox -P myprofile'

when starting each browser, console output will be captured and returned in
function metadata. Will wait for 2/5/10 seconds and check if the browsers have
been started. If all browsers can't be started, will return 500; otherwise will
return 200 but report the browsers that failed to start to the STDERR.

